main event: Two pilots flying T-33 aircraft at 10,000 feet spotted white smoke over the water, leading to the observation of what appeared to be two fast-moving vessels.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 3 minutes., The objects were observed making sharp turns at high speed., One observer thought the vessels resembled submarines., Large orange objects were spotted beneath the surface after the vessels disappeared., Weather conditions during the observation included slightly hazy visibility and high cirrus clouds.
sighted object: two fast-moving vessels and several large orange objects underwater
witness description: pilots of the 8th TAG FIR WG
